First, convert to a mixed number: $\frac{5}{3} = 1\frac{2}{3}$.

This tells us $\frac{5}{3}$ is between 1 and 2. Divide the interval 
from 1 to 2 into thirds. Count two-thirds of the way from 1 toward 2.

